Vice President Kamala Harris held a teleconference with community activists during Pride Month to discuss the ongoing fight for LGBTQ+ rights. She emphasized the need for continuous conversations and actions in support of equality and fairness. Harris shared her personal history of working on LGBTQ+ issues, including establishing a Hate Crimes Unit and organizing training to defeat the trans panic defense. She also highlighted the importance of passing the Equality Act and addressing the numerous anti-LGBTQ+ bills being proposed across the country. Harris mentioned specific actions taken by the Biden administration, such as repealing the ban on transgender people serving in the military and extending protections for transgender youth in education. She expressed gratitude for the activists' leadership and courage and acknowledged the importance of their voices in the fight for equality.